question: The "Cabrits National Park" is located in which country?
explanation: The Cabrits National Park is a national park located in the Cabrits Peninsula of the island country of Dominica, officially the Commonwealth of Dominica. This national park houses tropical forest, coral reefs and wetlands. This national park, established in 1986, has an extinct volcano. This national park is the last stop of Waitukubuli Trail and houses Fort Shirley, a former English military out spot.
